-- Twelve People Killed in Thai Chemical Plant Blast, Ministry Says
-- B y   S u p u n n a b u l   S u w a n n a k i j
-- 2012-05-06T17:00:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/twelve-people-killed-in-thai-chemical-plant-blast-ministry-says.html
Twelve people were killed and 125
injured in a blast at a chemical plant in  Thailand  operated by
Bangkok Synthetics Co., the public health ministry said.  The blast occurred at the BST Elastomers plant in Rayong,
about 180 kilometers (110 miles) southeast of Bangkok, the
ministry said today in a statement. A separate  statement  from
the company said eight people died and 122 were injured.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Supunnabul Suwannakij in Bangkok at 
 ssuwannakij@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
